Remarks.
This species is coupled with 

C
. 
sulawesiana

in the molecular phylogenetic tree (BP = 87; 
Fig. 2
) and the cladogram (BP = 100; 
Fig. 13
), and shares the oviscapt longer than the phallus (apodeme + sheath) as a synapomorphy (ch.49-1) with it. However, they can be distinguished from each other by their diagnostic characters.

